sekt.sem:
As a rule, arrow pointers is reserved for internal references;
     exceptios do exist, howewer, e.g. between notes for the two parts of Enten – Eller, between the 10 issues of Øieblikket and others.
     The short title of the target (i.e. the text between the two first /s of the target attribute) is rendered between the arrow and the page and line number, except that this is omitted in SKS-B whenever source and target is printed in the same volume so that the page and line number becomes unique.

